explanation:
Agent A's report is correct for the project configuration they described. If OS_DEBUG is defined as an empty macro so that the source line
    OS_DEBUG("No free RT signals to use for simulated time base\n");
preprocesses to just an empty statement (';'), that statement is executed but has no effect and its removal would not change program behaviour. Under the quoted MISRA C:2023 Rule 2.2 (no dead code) this is dead code in that project configuration and therefore a violation. Note: this conclusion depends on the project configuration. If in some build configurations OS_DEBUG expands to code with side effects, then the statement may not be dead for the project as a whole; the rule applies to the project as built, so the verifier must confirm the macro is empty in the relevant project configuration.
